aiden Newton (Dorset), both of which are recorded as  <i>Natton</i> and  <i>Netton</i> in the 13th century. The place-names derive from Old English  <i>nēat</i> ‘cattle’ +  <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’. There has probably been some confusion with   Noton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Natton","meanings":["English: variant of both   Notton   and   Noton  ."]},{"name":"Noton","meanings":["English: locative name from Notton (WR Yorks), which is recorded as  <i>Notone</i> in 1086 and  <i>Nocton</i> in 1230. The place-name derives from Old English  <i>hnoc</i> ‘wether sheep’ +  <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’. There has probably been some confusion with   Notton  , and perhaps also with   Knutton   and   Nocton  ."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":105,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":114,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Roger De Notton was born in 1110, in Notton, Yorkshire, England as the son of Gilbert De Notton. He married Mrs Roger de Notton. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1110–":"1110–Surnud","1105–Male":"1105–Surnud","1110–Male":"1110–Surnud","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1070–Male":"1070–Surnud","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1115":"1115","1224":"1224","1110":"1110","1142":"1142","1070":"1070","Notton, Yorkshire, England":"Notton, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1110–":"1110–Kuollut","1105–Male":"1105–Kuollut","1110–Male":"1110–Kuollut","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1142–Female":"1142–Kuollut","1070–Male":"1070–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1115":"1115","1224":"1224","1110":"1110","1142":"1142","1070":"1070","Notton, Yorkshire, England":"Notton, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1110–":"1110–Décédé","1105–Male":"1105–Décédé","1110–Male":"1110–Décédé","1115–Female":"1115–Décédée","1142–Female":"1142–Décédée","1070–Male":"1070–Décédé","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1115":"1115","1224":"1224","1110":"1110","1142":"1142","1070":"1070","Notton, Yorkshire, England":"Notton, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Roger De Notton est né en 1110, à Notton, Everwyck, Angleterre, fils de Gilbert De Notton. Il a épousé Mrs Roger de Notton. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1110–":"1110–Verstorben","1105–Male":"1105–Verstorben","1110–Male":"1110–Verstorben","1115–Female":"1115–Verstorben","1142–Female":"1142–Verstorben","1070–Male